/target
examples/*/target
# v0.22.6: `coral skill build` default output directory.
/dist
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock.bak
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
.coral-cache.json
**/.coral-cache.json
.claude/
# v0.34 onboarding §11 decision #6: dogfood the Coral marketplace on
# this repo itself so contributors who clone + open Claude Code see
# the plugin offered. Everything else under .claude/ (local IDE
# state, scheduled-tasks locks, settings.local.json overrides) stays
# ignored — only this one shared file ships.
!.claude/settings.json
# Coral file-locking sidecars (v0.15+) — empty inodes for flock(2)
**/index.md.lock
**/log.md.lock
**/.coral-embeddings.json.lock
.coral/sessions/*.jsonl
.coral/sessions/*.lock
.coral/sessions/index.json
!.coral/sessions/distilled/
# FR-ONB-34 (security-critical): catch-all so an accidental
# `.coral/config.toml` with an Anthropic API key never gets staged.
# Comes AFTER the per-pattern allowlist so `!.coral/sessions/distilled/`
# still wins. Bootstrap checkpoint may include LLM-token usage metadata.
.coral/
.wiki/.bootstrap-state.json
.wiki/.bootstrap.lock
# v0.35 Phase C (P-H1): coral-ui/build.rs pre-compresses the SPA
# bundle into .gz / .br siblings on every cargo build. These are
# pure build artifacts — committing them would churn on every UI
# rebuild and gain nothing (the binary picks them up via
# include_dir! at compile time).
crates/coral-ui/assets/dist/**/*.gz
crates/coral-ui/assets/dist/**/*.br
# v0.36 hardening: build.rs drops the heavy raw JS bundles (>=100 KiB)
# after writing their .br/.gz siblings, so the resulting binary is
# ~500 KiB smaller. The raw .js files are regenerated by `npm run
# build` from assets/src/; tracking them in git only churns on every
# JS rebuild. The lightweight raw assets (index.css, favicon.svg,
# index.html) stay tracked because they're below the threshold and
# are needed for `cargo check` on a fresh clone with no npm step.
crates/coral-ui/assets/dist/assets/*.js
